<chapter xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"  xml:id="chapter-radical-expressions-and-equations">
  <title>Radical Expressions and Equations</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      Radicals like <m>\sqrt[3]{\phantom{x}}</m> are the notation we use for a math operation that
      is the opposite process from raising to a power. Just like exponents, there are valid (and not
      valid) ways to combine radical expressions and end with a simpler expression. This chapter
      covers these <q>rules</q> for radicals as well as a few other related topics.
    </p>
  </introduction>
